  "extra_note_en": "Pretérito Perfeito: specific, finished actions (yesterday, last year, once upon a time). Pretérito Imperfeito: descriptions, background, habits (when I was young, it was raining, he used to play). Irregulars in Perfeito are very common: ser (fui, foste, foi, fomos, foram), ir (fui, foste, foi, fomos, foram), ter (tive, tiveste, teve, tivemos, tiveram), fazer (fiz, fizeste, fez, fizemos, fizeram), dizer (disse, disseste, disse, dissemos, disseram), ver (vi, viste, viu, vimos, viram), vir (vim, vieste, veio, viemos, vieram), estar (estive, estiveste, esteve, estivemos, estiveram), poder (pude, pudeste, pôde, pudemos, puderam). Time expressions: ontem (yesterday), na semana passada (last week), quando era criança (when I was a child), sempre (always – for habits in imperfeito), etc."
}